<item>
            <title>[LU-11892] Memory leak in MDT Coordinator</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-11892</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;After creating a big HSM request candidate list, coordinator thread&lt;br/&gt;
 allocates an update list which is 16 bytes times the number of&lt;br/&gt;
 candidates files. In some cases, they could be more than 300,000&lt;br/&gt;
 candidate files and so several MB will be needed.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Memory allocation failure was skipping candidate list freeing which led to memory leak.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;&#160;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This problem was detected under Lustre 2.10.5. Since, a patch landed that makes this bug&#160; more difficult to trigger, but the code is still present.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I will submit a fix for it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
